The reason I changed the input parameter "even_cows" from 0 to 1 is that: during page fault, the mapping (struct adress_space) the fault page used is the mapping of the underlying filesystem (i.e. ext4) inode, not the one of the Lustre inode.
Thus when call unmap_mapping_range, it will skip the page mapped user space address in unmap_mapping_range() ...->zap_pte_range()

/*
				 * unmap_shared_mapping_pages() wants to
				 * invalidate cache without truncating:
				 * unmap shared but keep private pages.
				 */
				if (details->check_mapping &&
				    details->check_mapping != page->mapping)
					continue;

