Patch Set 13:

We can check whether whether the file is cached in PCC in pcc_layout_invalidate() as follows:
-void pcc_layout_invalidate(struct inode *inode)
+bool pcc_layout_invalidate(struct inode *inode)
 {
        struct pcc_inode *pcci;
+       bool cached = false;

        ENTRY;

@@ -2108,10 +2111,10 @@ void pcc_layout_invalidate(struct inode *inode)
                       PFID(&ll_i2info(inode)->lli_fid), pcci->pcci_layout_gen);

                pcc_inode_put(pcci);
+               cached = true;
        }
        pcc_inode_unlock(inode);
-
-       EXIT;
+       RETURN(cached);
 }

sanity-pcc.sh test_4 failed when two client mmap read/write a file.
As RW-PCC cached file is actual a HSM released file, thus if a file is RW-PCC cached on a client, the remote client will treat it as a HSM released file. Thus it could disable the remote client to mmap a file when LOV found it was a HSM released file.

we could disable mmap functionality when the page is mapped in PCC by setting *cached = false in pcc_fault, thus the normal Lustre IO path will restore the HSM released file and the IO directs to normal Lustre IO path after restore.
